Enable the proxy

Go to Settings > Network.
Enable Proxy for TCP.
(Recommended) To proxy traffic to internal DNS resolvers, select UDP.
(Recommended) To proxy traffic for diagnostic tools such as ping and traceroute, select ICMP. You may also need to update your system to allow ICMP traffic through cloudflared:

 Linux


Ensure that ping_group_range includes the Group ID (GID) of the user running cloudflared.

To get the Group ID of the user, run id -g.
To verify the Group IDs that are allowed to use ICMP:

Terminal windowsudo sysctl net.ipv4.ping_group_range
